      "writtenOn": "2020-12-08T13:32:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Food for thought (aka TODO):\n* how should we store that CV has lost access to a tryjob due to change of ACLs?\n* for newly created Build entity which doesn\u0027t have external ID yet, ie about to be scheduled, what is status?\n  * -\u003e and how do we store lack of ACLs to schedule such build?\n\nMaybe NO_READ_ACCESS, TO_BE_SCHEDULED, NO_SCHEDULE_ACCESS will be good enough, but i\u0027m not sure yet.",
      "revId": "d61fdcf231a9b2ef4f325952e489c850cb34af59",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c02cb045_122adee5",
        "filename": "cv/internal/tryjob/storage.proto",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 25,
      "author": {
        "id": 1381059
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-12-08T20:42:26Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Good point\n\n\u003e Food for thought (aka TODO):\n\u003e * how should we store that CV has lost access to a tryjob due to change of ACLs?\n\nI\u0027m thinking of marking this as FAILURE and having a FailureDetails/StatusDetails-ish message to explain which type of failure it is. But NO_READ_ACCESS enum value would also suffice.\n\n\u003e * for newly created Build entity which doesn\u0027t have external ID yet, ie about to be scheduled, what is status?\n\nMy thought is PENDING, but PENDING is now overloaded with two meanings, maybe we can split it by:\n  * PENDING_SCHEDULED: CV hasn\u0027t scheduled this Tryjob in the external system yet.\n  * PENDING_STARTED: CV has scheduled this Tryjob but it hasn\u0027t started in the external system yet.\n\n\u003e   * -\u003e and how do we store lack of ACLs to schedule such build?\n\nSame as losing read access. Either mark it as failure and explain the failure somewhere else or creating new enum value as suggested below.\n\n\u003e \n\u003e Maybe NO_READ_ACCESS, TO_BE_SCHEDULED, NO_SCHEDULE_ACCESS will be good enough, but i\u0027m not sure yet.\n\nWDYT of two types of failure?\n  * INTERNAL_FAILURE: e.g. CV losing access\n  * EXTERNAL_FAILURE: Status reported by BB.",
      "parentUuid": "118744df_6cb7b9b7",
      "revId": "d61fdcf231a9b2ef4f325952e489c850cb34af59",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "0ed22ebc_a6bbf6ad",
        "filename": "cv/internal/tryjob/storage.proto",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 36,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114919
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-12-08T13:32:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "So, did you mean this to be externally reported or possibly set purely on CV\u0027s whim regardless of external system?\n\nFor just BB, externally reported will suffice, because CancelBuild() RPC will respond with final the Build status with status\u003dbb.Canceled, it\u0027ll be easy to only set CANCELED here iff bb.build.status is canceled.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 34,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 36,
        "endChar": 15
      },
      "revId": "d61fdcf231a9b2ef4f325952e489c850cb34af59",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
